Juan Cuevas Perales (Guadassuar, 8 February 1782–1855) was a Valencian composer in the Classical style.

He was a Chapel  choirboy in Valencia. His first known professional employment was as choirmaster at church of  in Valencia in a post which he held from 1801 to 1804, when he came back to cathedral.

He obtained the position of Chapel master in the cathedral of Tortosa in February 1817 and moved there, but days before he asked and won the same post at  in Xàtiva.

